h.gif" /><br><br>I am playing around with setting up banks of hotkeys, though. My problem always has been hotkey space, since I generally use one set at a time and put most of my spell gems in. Now I'm putting announcement hotkeys in a separate set. The difference is, of course, having to announce when a spell <i>starts</i> (as in heals) as opposed to announcing when it <i>lands</i>. I suppose I should just Alt-# to cast the spells, but I usually confuse it and use Shift instead, and wonder why I'm not casting anything.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Dear President Bush,<br><br>Please don't get us all killed.<br><br>Yours (for another four years),<br>The American People</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from New York (no, not the city)</td></tr></table>
